#compdef mstream
# ============================================================================
# mstream - self-hosted music streaming server +
#            Electron desktop application
#            (Node.js, GPL-3.0)
#
# Author : Iros (IrosTheBeggar)
# Upstream: https://github.com/IrosTheBeggar/mStream
# npm    : mstream (binary: mstream)
#
# `mStream` is a self-hosted music streaming
# server alongside an Electron desktop app that
# wraps the same server with a native GUI. The
# server scans a configured music library
# directory + serves audio file streaming +
# album-art + playlist management + multi-user
# authentication via JWT + a Progressive Web App
# (PWA) frontend. Use cases:
#   - Self-hosted Spotify-equivalent for personal
#     music collections (free of Spotify's
#     algorithmic interference + cloud-only
#     licensing limits)
#   - Family-sharing music library access
#     (one user serves files; family members
#     stream from any device)
#   - Personal-music-collection backend for
#     mobile apps via mStream's REST API
#   - Mobile-friendly streaming via the bundled
#     PWA (works offline + supports background
#     playback on iOS + Android)
#   - Plex/Jellyfin alternative for
#     audio-only collections
#
# Architecture:
#   - Express.js HTTP server
#   - music-metadata for audio file tag
#     extraction (ID3v2 + Vorbis comments + FLAC
#     metadata + AAC tags)
#   - jimp for image processing (album art
#     resizing + thumbnail generation)
#   - jsonwebtoken for JWT-based authentication
#   - busboy for multipart file uploads
#   - archiver for ZIP-bundle album downloads
#   - undici for outbound HTTP (Last.fm scrobbling,
#     etc.)
#   - electron-updater for desktop auto-update
#   - winston for structured logging
#   - ws for WebSocket-based real-time sync
#   - Optional Rust sidecar processes
#     (`rust-parser` + `rust-server-audio`) for
#     high-performance metadata parsing + audio
#     transcoding
#
# Usage:
#   mstream [options]
#
# Flags (manually-parsed in cli-boot-wrapper.js;
# only three flags exist):
#   -V, --version                  - print
#                                     version
#                                     and exit
#   -j, --json <file>              - JSON
#                                     boot/config
#                                     file path
#                                     (default
#                                     save/conf/
#                                     default.json
#                                     relative
#                                     to the
#                                     mstream
#                                     install
#                                     directory)
#       --json=<file>              - alternate
#                                     single-
#                                     token form
#                                     of -j
#   -h, --help                     - display
#                                     help and
#                                     exit
#
# Example invocation:
#   mstream
#     # boot with default save/conf/default.json
#   mstream -j /etc/mstream/production.json
#     # boot with custom config
#   mstream --json=/etc/mstream/staging.json
#     # equivalent
#
# Example save/conf/default.json:
#   {
#     "port": 3000,
#     "userinterface": "webapp",
#     "storage": {
#       "albumArtDirectory": "image-cache",
#       "dbDirectory": "save/db"
#     },
#     "folders": {
#       "My Music": {
#         "root": "/home/user/Music"
#       }
#     },
#     "users": {
#       "alice": {
#         "password": "<bcrypt-hashed-password>",
#         "vpaths": ["My Music"],
#         "guest": false
#       }
#     },
#     "secret": "<random-jwt-secret>",
#     "noUpload": false,
#     "scanOptions": {
#       "scanInterval": 24,
#       "saveInterval": 30,
#       "pause": 0,
#       "skipImg": false,
#       "bootScanDelay": 30,
#       "skipDuplicateChecking": false
#     }
#   }
#
# When run inside Electron (`process.versions.
# electron` is set), mstream defers to the
# build/electron.js entry point instead, which
# provides the native desktop UI.
#
# The music-metadata lane is built on `music-
# metadata ^11.11.1` (declared verbatim at
# upstream package.json HEAD as a direct dep,
# imported by the mStream file-scanner module
# during library indexing to extract per-file
# tags (artist + album + title + track number +
# year + genre + duration + bitrate + sample
# rate + album art binary blobs)), the canonical
# Node multi-format audio metadata reader by
# Bo Schwarzstein (Borewit) - github.com/Borewit/
# music-metadata.
#
# Bo Schwarzstein's music-metadata is the
# de-facto canonical Node audio-metadata library:
#   - Used by 4,000+ npm packages
#   - 700,000+ weekly npm downloads
#   - Multi-format support: MP3 (ID3v1 + ID3v2.2/3/4)
#     + Ogg (Ogg Vorbis + Ogg FLAC + Ogg Opus) +
#     FLAC (native FLAC tags + embedded ID3v2) +
#     M4A/AAC (iTunes-style atoms) + WAV (RIFF +
#     ID3v2) + AIFF + DSF + WV + AC3 + EAC3 + WMA
#     + Matroska/WebM
#   - Streaming + buffer + URL + file-handle
#     input interfaces
#   - Album art extraction (multiple images per
#     file)
#   - Pure-JavaScript implementation (no native
#     dependencies; works in Cloudflare Workers
#     + Vercel Edge Runtime + Deno + Bun)
#   - TypeScript typings
#   - Browser + Node + Deno + Bun + Electron
#     isomorphic
#
# music-metadata's distinguishing position vs
# alternatives:
#   - music-metadata (Borewit): canonical;
#     multi-format; pure-JS; THIS AXIS
#   - node-id3: ID3v2-specific; less format
#     coverage
#   - jsmediatags: MP3 + FLAC + MP4; less
#     active maintenance
#   - ffprobe-static: shell-out to ffprobe;
#     requires ffmpeg binary
#   - node-ffmetadata: ffmpeg-based; slower
#     than pure-JS music-metadata
#
# music-metadata's canonical status comes from:
#   1. Pure-JavaScript implementation (no native
#      addons + no ffmpeg dependency)
#   2. Broadest format coverage in the Node
#      ecosystem
#   3. Most-active maintenance (Borewit ships
#      regular updates + bug fixes)
#   4. TypeScript typings + extensive test
#      coverage
#   5. Used by major music players + streaming
#     servers (mStream + Hyperamp + Hypeampe +
#     hypermodules' broader audio ecosystem)
#
# Bo Schwarzstein's broader Node ecosystem
# footprint (the Borewit-authored multi-library
# audio metadata umbrella):
#   - music-metadata (canonical Node audio
#     metadata; THIS AXIS)
#   - peek-readable (binary file format
#     peeking utility; foundation of music-
#     metadata's binary parser)
#   - strtok3 (binary tokenizer for streaming
#     binary parsing)
#   - token-types (binary token type
#     definitions for strtok3)
#   - file-type (canonical Node file-type
#     detector; identifies binary files by
#     magic-number signatures; widely used)
#   - readable-web-to-node-stream (Web Streams
#     <-> Node Streams adapter)
#
# Borewit's role in the Node ecosystem is
# *binary-file-format-parser canonical
# infrastructure* - similar to:
#   - Vitaly Puzrin (nodeca; document formats:
#     YAML + Markdown + zlib + XML)
#   - Sergey Belov (svgo team; SVG optimization)
#   - Stuart Knightley (jszip; ZIP)
#
# Borewit's canonical position spans the
# *binary audio/file format detection +
# metadata extraction + streaming binary
# parsing* vertical.
#
# mStream uses music-metadata in the file
# scanner module:
#   ```js
#   const mm = require('music-metadata');
#
#   async function scanFile(filepath) {
#     const metadata = await mm.parseFile(filepath, {
#       skipCovers: false,
#       skipPostHeaders: false,
#     });
#     return {
#       title: metadata.common.title,
#       artist: metadata.common.artist,
#       album: metadata.common.album,
#       year: metadata.common.year,
#       genre: metadata.common.genre,
#       duration: metadata.format.duration,
#       bitrate: metadata.format.bitrate,
#       sampleRate: metadata.format.sampleRate,
#       picture: metadata.common.picture?.[0],
#     };
#   }
#   ```
# The extracted metadata is persisted to the
# server's SQLite database for fast library
# browsing + search.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 271 :: Audio codec / decoding libraries
#              (multi-format audio file decoding
#              + container parsing + metadata
#              extraction for music players +
#              audio analysis + format-conversion
#              tooling)
# Round 1513 :: TS-Node slot 3 of 4 :: CLOSES Axis 271
#                                       (264th axis closed)
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : pdeljanov/Symphonia        [R1511 _psst-cli]
#             (Philip Deljanov; canonical
#              Rust multi-codec decoding
#              framework)
#   Go      : hajimehoshi/oto            [R1512 _goboy]
#             (Hajime Hoshi; canonical
#              Go cross-platform audio
#              output)
#   TS/Node : Borewit/music-metadata     [R1513 THIS FILE]
#             (Bo Schwarzstein /
#              Borewit; canonical Node
#              multi-format audio
#              metadata reader)
#
# Borewit/music-metadata closes Axis 271 with
# the *metadata-extraction-canonical* pattern.
# The three lanes occupy DIFFERENT positions
# in the audio pipeline:
#
#   - Rust (Symphonia): decoder (bytes -> PCM
#     samples; full multi-codec framework)
#   - Go (oto): output (PCM samples -> hardware
#     audio devices)
#   - Node (music-metadata): metadata extraction
#     (file -> tag dictionary + format info)
#
# This is the *complementary-pipeline-trifecta*
# pattern unique to Axis 271 - each lane's
# canonical occupies a different position in
# the audio processing pipeline:
#   - Input stage (decoder): Symphonia
#   - Output stage (player): oto
#   - Metadata stage (tagger): music-metadata
#
# No other axis in the corpus has this
# pipeline-position split. Most axes have
# parallel-canonicals (each language's
# canonical does the same job). Audio is
# unusual in that the three languages'
# canonicals serve different stages of the
# audio workflow.
#
# This split reflects the divergent needs of
# each ecosystem's typical use cases:
#   - Rust: emulators + audio players + DAWs
#     (full pipeline; needs decoder)
#   - Go: games + emulators + sequencers (needs
#     low-latency output)
#   - Node: music servers + streaming + library
#     management (needs metadata + tagging)
#
# Cross-language interop at the PCM-sample +
# format-metadata level - all three canonicals
# work with byte-identical audio file inputs
# and produce byte-identical metadata + decoded
# samples (modulo decoder-specific dithering).
#
# Use-case spectrum across the three lanes:
#   - psst-cli (Rust, Symphonia): Spotify
#     Ogg Vorbis stream decoder + playback
#   - goboy (Go, oto): Game Boy emulator with
#     4-channel APU audio output
#   - mstream (Node, music-metadata): self-
#     hosted music streaming server with
#     library metadata indexing
#
# Three lanes, three audio-pipeline positions
# (decode + play + tag), three implementation
# strategies (multi-codec Rust framework +
# multi-platform Go output + pure-JS Node
# metadata extraction), all converging on
# the multi-format audio file ecosystem.
#
# Axis 271 closes the round 1513 cycle - 264th
# axis closed total. The Audio codec axis is
# the *first axis in the corpus to demonstrate
# the complementary-pipeline-trifecta pattern*
# where the three lanes occupy distinct stages
# of the same processing pipeline.
#
# Multi-axis canonical-Node author/org cohort
# (now spanning 15 distinct individuals/orgs):
#   - Sindre Sorhus (chalk + ~1000 microlibs)
#   - Matt Ranney + Redis Inc. (node-redis)
#   - Brian Carlson (node-postgres)
#   - Andrey Sitnik (PostCSS + browserslist +
#     nanoid)
#   - Lovell Fuller (sharp)
#   - Paul Miller (noble umbrella)
#   - Devon Govett (foliojs umbrella +
#     lightningcss)
#   - Matteo Collina + mqttjs org (undici +
#     pino + fastify + MQTT.js)
#   - Isaac Z. Schlueter (3 axes: globbing,
#     TAR, INI)
#   - Vitaly Puzrin + nodeca (js-yaml +
#     markdown-it + pako + argparse + sax +
#     linkify-it)
#   - Sergey Belov + svgo team (svg/svgo)
#   - Matt Zabriskie + axios team (axios)
#   - Stuart Knightley (jszip)
#   - Justin Latimer (node-midi)
#   - Bo Schwarzstein / Borewit (music-metadata
#     + peek-readable + strtok3 + token-types +
#     file-type + readable-web-to-node-stream;
#     THIS AXIS)
# ============================================================================

_mstream() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '(-V --version)'{-V,--version}'[print version and exit]' \
        '(-j --json)'{-j,--json}'[JSON boot/config file path]:file:_files -g "*.json"' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]'
}

_mstream "$@"
